Short Term:
 - Missing Firefox version bumping commits (hg->git conversion issue?)
 - Bundle files and about:config need actual version numbers
   - echo $TORBROWSER_VERSION into an input
 - Source integrity
   - More git repos need signed tags
 - Hardening options
   - http://wiki.debian.org/Hardening
   - Can we randomize stack canaries each release, etc?

Mid Term:
 - MacOS cross compilation?
   - Need Mac Skeleton and Mac Langpacks
   - https://launchpad.net/~flosoft/+archive/cross-apple/+packages
     - GCC 4.2.1 in these packages is too old and crashed during
       Firefox build. We need 4.5.1+.
     - GCC 4.7.3 build
       - ./configure --disable-shared --target=i686-apple-darwin10 \
         --prefix=/usr --with-sysroot=/usr/lib/apple/SDKs/MacOSX10.6.sdk \
         --with-slibdir=/usr/i686-apple-darwin10/lib \
         --mandir=/usr/i686-apple-darwin10/share/man \
         --infodir=/usr/i686-apple-darwin10/share/info --libexecdir=/usr/lib \
         --disable-nls --with-gxx-include-dir=/usr/include/c++/4.7.3 \
         --enable-version-specific-runtime-libs \
         --with-as=/usr/apple-osx/bin//i686-apple-darwin11-as \
         --with-ld=/usr/apple-osx/bin//i686-apple-darwin11-ld \
         --enable-languages=c,c++,objc,obj-c++
       - http://www.linuxforums.org/forum/applications/172812-solved-gcc-make-error-missing-libgcc-mvars.html
     - Current Status:
       - GCC 4.7.3 builds, but the odcctools ld does not support -no_compact_unwind
       - odcctools can't be recompiled with 64bit gcc:
         - https://code.google.com/p/iphone-dev/issues/detail?id=14
         - https://code.google.com/p/iphone-dev/issues/detail?id=37
   - Fedora route:
     - Source: https://github.com/mingwandroid/toolchain4
     - Binaries: https://code.google.com/p/mingw-and-ndk/downloads/list
     - Info/Discussion:
       - https://lists.macosforge.org/pipermail/macports-dev/2011-September/016210.html
       - http://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=50229
     - Current Status:
       - Included GCC does not support -arch (even though it claims to)
       - GCC 4.7.3 builds using the binutils in the above binary link, but
         resulting gcc tries to link with -lgcc_ext.10.5, which does not exist.
   - http://wiki.freepascal.org/Cross_compiling_OSX_on_Linux
     - Git instead of SVN: https://github.com/mazhe/odcctools
 - Fix windows issues:
   - Link to DirectX via Wine (for WebGL)
     - Weird C++ stdext namespace issues remain :/
   - Accesibility still fails :/
     - https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=815581
       - Has conflicts with FF17-ESR :/
       - Can we just pull the whole accessibility dir?
 - If Tor Launcher fails to load, the browser still can launch
   - Missing/Partial Localization strings can cause this..
   - I think we don't care? Torbutton's new tor test should fail..

Long Term:
 - Offline building
   - Requires special VM setup.
 - Compile the toolchain, too?
   - Doing so might allow us to build deterministically
     using other Linux distributions as our base image
     - Defense in depth against distribution-wide compromise
     - Though we may still have issues with linking against
       OS shared libraries if the versions don't match.
       - Build them too? Or is it safe to ship reference link
         stubs?
 - FIPS-140?
